it is closed: . The important feature of
the symplectic form () is that it is gauge
invariant. Using the transformation rule ()
and cyclicity of the trace, we easily find [_a,_b]=[a,b]  . 
It follows that the gauge group  acts symplectically on
the affine space . Since  is contractible, there
exists a corresponding moment map 
